Interface FluxClient


  • public interface FluxClient
    The client for the new data scripting language centered on querying and manipulating time series data.

List<FluxTable> query(@Nonnull

      • query

           String query,
           @Nonnull
           BiConsumer<FluxClient.Cancellable,FluxRecord> onNext,
           @Nonnull
           Runnable onComplete,
           @Nonnull
           Consumer<? super Throwable> onError)
        Execute a Flux query against the InfluxDB and asynchronous stream FluxRecords to onNext.
        Parameters:
        query - the flux query to execute
        onNext - callback to consume result which are matched the query with capability to discontinue a streaming query
        onComplete - callback to consume a notification about successfully end of stream
        onError - callback to consume any error notification

      • raw

        void raw(@Nonnull
         String query,
         @Nonnull
         BiConsumer<FluxClient.Cancellable,String> onResponse,
         @Nonnull
         Runnable onComplete,
         @Nonnull
         Consumer<? super Throwable> onError)
        Execute a Flux query against the InfluxDB and asynchronous stream the lines to onResponse.
        Parameters:
        query - the flux query to execute
        onResponse - callback to consume the raw response which are matched the query. The callback call contains the one line of the response.
        onComplete - callback to consume a notification about successfully end of stream
        onError - callback to consume any error notification
